The book &quot;Practical Java&quot; by Haggar explains why you should probably want to
do your equals method this way:

class Worker extends Person 
{
....
public boolean equals(Object o) 
{
  if (o == null) 
  {
    return false;
  }
  if ( o.getClass().equals( this.getClass() ) )
  {
    Worker w = (Worker) o;
    return name.equals( w.name ) && doList.equals( w.doList ); 
  }
  return false;
}

...
}


